The paper deals with table extraction from unstructured digital files, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image processing and natural language processing (NLP) techniques for text extraction. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel graph-based convolutional neural network model, which falls under the category of deep learning (DL) and can be considered as a contribution to the field of machine learning (ML). Hence, cs.CL, cs.LG, and cs.DL are also likely sub-categories.
